      <title>H.R. 6408</title>
      <link>https://www.govtrack.us/congress/bills/118/hr6408/summary</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.govtrack.us/congress/bills/118/hr6408/summary</guid>
      <pubDate>Mon, 15 Apr 2024 10:15:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <description> 		 			&lt;h4 class="event_title"&gt;Bill Summary&lt;/h4&gt; 			&lt;div class="event_body"&gt; 				&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.govtrack.us/congress/bills/118/hr6408/summary" &gt;H.R. 6408: To amend the Internal Revenue Code of 1986 to terminate the tax-exempt status of terrorist supporting organizations.&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt; 			&lt;/div&gt; 		  		&lt;div class="event_date"&gt; 			&lt;span&gt;Date: &lt;/span&gt; 			 				Apr 15, 2024 10:15 a.m. 			 		&lt;/div&gt;  		 		 		&lt;div class="event_body"&gt; 			 			 			&lt;p&gt;According to the &lt;a href="https://www.cbo.gov/publication/59923#:%7E:text=Summary,State%20as%20a%20terrorist%20organization."&gt;Congressional Budget Office&lt;/a&gt;, “H.R. 6408 would suspend the tax-exempt status of organizations that support terrorism. Under current law, an entity’s tax-exempt status is suspended if it is designated by the Department of State as a terrorist organization. H.R. 6408 would extend that prohibition to include organizations identified as having provided material support or resources to a terrorist or terrorist-supporting organization within the prior three years. The bill would establish procedures for the department to provide notice …&lt;/p&gt; 		&lt;/div&gt; </description>
      <media:content url="https://www.govtrack.us/congress/bills/118/hr6408/thumbnail" type="application/octet-stream"/>
      <category>Bill Summary</category>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>H.R. 6015</title>
      <link>https://www.govtrack.us/congress/bills/118/hr6015/summary</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.govtrack.us/congress/bills/118/hr6015/summary</guid>
      <pubDate>Mon, 15 Apr 2024 10:12:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <description> 		 			&lt;h4 class="event_title"&gt;Bill Summary&lt;/h4&gt; 			&lt;div class="event_body"&gt; 				&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.govtrack.us/congress/bills/118/hr6015/summary" &gt;H.R. 6015: Iran Sanctions Accountability Act of 2023&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt; 			&lt;/div&gt; 		  		&lt;div class="event_date"&gt; 			&lt;span&gt;Date: &lt;/span&gt; 			 				Apr 15, 2024 10:12 a.m. 			 		&lt;/div&gt;  		 		 		&lt;div class="event_body"&gt; 			 			 			&lt;p&gt;According to the &lt;a href="https://www.cbo.gov/publication/59796#:%7E:text=Summary,the%20efficacy%20of%20those%20regulations."&gt;Congressional Budget Office&lt;/a&gt;, “H.R. 6015 would require the Administration to issue regulations to ensure that humanitarian exceptions to sanctions on Iran do not facilitate international terrorism or the proliferation of weapons of mass destruction. The bill would require periodic reports on the efficacy of those regulations. It also would direct the United States Executive Director at the World Bank to oppose financial assistance to Iran.”&lt;/p&gt;  		&lt;/div&gt; </description>
      <media:content url="https://www.govtrack.us/congress/bills/118/hr6015/thumbnail" type="application/octet-stream"/>
      <category>Bill Summary</category>
    </item>
