    <item>
      <title>H.R. 4016</title>
      <link>https://www.govtrack.us/congress/bills/118/hr4016/summary</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.govtrack.us/congress/bills/118/hr4016/summary</guid>
      <pubDate>Sun, 14 Apr 2024 12:46:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <description> 		 			&lt;h4 class="event_title"&gt;Bill Summary&lt;/h4&gt; 			&lt;div class="event_body"&gt; 				&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.govtrack.us/congress/bills/118/hr4016/summary" &gt;H.R. 4016: Veteran Fraud Reimbursement Act&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt; 			&lt;/div&gt; 		  		&lt;div class="event_date"&gt; 			&lt;span&gt;Date: &lt;/span&gt; 			 				Apr 14, 2024 12:46 p.m. 			 		&lt;/div&gt;  		 		 		&lt;div class="event_body"&gt; 			 			 			&lt;p&gt;For those veterans who become unable to manage their VA benefits, the &lt;a href="https://www.benefits.va.gov/fiduciary/index.asp"&gt;VA has a program in which another person can serve as a fiduciary&lt;/a&gt; to help the veteran. However, as with anything, there's the potential for fraud. This bill would provide for reimbursement to veterans defrauded by fiduciaries.&lt;/p&gt;  		&lt;/div&gt; </description>
      <media:content url="https://www.govtrack.us/congress/bills/118/hr4016/thumbnail" type="application/octet-stream"/>
      <category>Bill Summary</category>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>H.R. 4824</title>
      <link>https://www.govtrack.us/congress/bills/118/hr4824/summary</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.govtrack.us/congress/bills/118/hr4824/summary</guid>
      <pubDate>Sun, 14 Apr 2024 12:38:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <description> 		 			&lt;h4 class="event_title"&gt;Bill Summary&lt;/h4&gt; 			&lt;div class="event_body"&gt; 				&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.govtrack.us/congress/bills/118/hr4824/summary" &gt;H.R. 4824: Carbon Sequestration Collaboration Act&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt; 			&lt;/div&gt; 		  		&lt;div class="event_date"&gt; 			&lt;span&gt;Date: &lt;/span&gt; 			 				Apr 14, 2024 12:38 p.m. 			 		&lt;/div&gt;  		 		 		&lt;div class="event_body"&gt; 			 			 			&lt;p&gt;This bill would direct the Secretary of Energy to start performing carbon sequestration work and evaluating the effects of it. According to the U.S. Geological Survey, &lt;a href="https://www.usgs.gov/faqs/whats-difference-between-geologic-and-biologic-carbon-sequestration"&gt;carbon sequestration can be divided into geologic and biologic sequestration&lt;/a&gt;. The former often can assist oil wells which are no longer producing at high levels to produce more oil. Geologic sequestration involves forcing CO2 into geologic formations while biologic generally refers to growing more vegetation, like trees, which can capture and store carbon.&lt;/p&gt;  		&lt;/div&gt; </description>
      <media:content url="https://www.govtrack.us/congress/bills/118/hr4824/thumbnail" type="application/octet-stream"/>
      <category>Bill Summary</category>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>H.R. 529</title>
      <link>https://www.govtrack.us/congress/bills/118/hr529/summary</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.govtrack.us/congress/bills/118/hr529/summary</guid>
      <pubDate>Sun, 14 Apr 2024 12:29:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <description> 		 			&lt;h4 class="event_title"&gt;Bill Summary&lt;/h4&gt; 			&lt;div class="event_body"&gt; 				&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.govtrack.us/congress/bills/118/hr529/summary" &gt;H.R. 529: Extending Limits of U.S. Customs Waters Act&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt; 			&lt;/div&gt; 		  		&lt;div class="event_date"&gt; 			&lt;span&gt;Date: &lt;/span&gt; 			 				Apr 14, 2024 12:29 p.m. 			 		&lt;/div&gt;  		 		 		&lt;div class="event_body"&gt; 			 			 			&lt;p&gt;This bill would change the current limit of U.S. "customs waters" from 12 miles to 24 miles. This would double the distance from shore that &lt;a href="https://www.cbp.gov/about/congressional-resources/testimony/statement-record-customs-water"&gt;Customs and Border Protection could operate&lt;/a&gt;. If passed, it would bring U.S. Customs authorizations into alignment with Presidential Proclamations from 1988 and 1999.&lt;/p&gt;  		&lt;/div&gt; </description>
      <media:content url="https://www.govtrack.us/congress/bills/118/hr529/thumbnail" type="application/octet-stream"/>
      <category>Bill Summary</category>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>H.R. 1792</title>
      <link>https://www.govtrack.us/congress/bills/118/hr1792/summary</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.govtrack.us/congress/bills/118/hr1792/summary</guid>
      <pubDate>Fri, 05 Apr 2024 15:28:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <description> 		 			&lt;h4 class="event_title"&gt;Bill Summary&lt;/h4&gt; 			&lt;div class="event_body"&gt; 				&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.govtrack.us/congress/bills/118/hr1792/summary" &gt;H.R. 1792: South Pacific Tuna Treaty Act of 2023&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt; 			&lt;/div&gt; 		  		&lt;div class="event_date"&gt; 			&lt;span&gt;Date: &lt;/span&gt; 			 				Apr 5, 2024 3:28 p.m. 			 		&lt;/div&gt;  		 		 		&lt;div class="event_body"&gt; 			 			 			&lt;p&gt;This bill "&lt;a href="https://www.seafoodsource.com/news/premium/supply-trade/us-bill-would-enact-changes-made-to-south-pacific-tuna-treaty-in-2016"&gt;would remedy differences between amendments made to the South Pacific Tuna Treaty in 2016 and current U.S. law&lt;/a&gt;." The bill has strong support from the U. S. tuna fishing industry. Per its sponsor, in particular it would &lt;a href="https://radewagen.house.gov/media-center/press-releases/committee-passes-amata-s-south-pacific-tuna-treaty-act"&gt;stabilize high-seas fishing days&lt;/a&gt; and codify access to various island nations’ Exclusive Economic Zone waters.&lt;/p&gt;  		&lt;/div&gt; </description>
      <media:content url="https://www.govtrack.us/congress/bills/118/hr1792/thumbnail" type="application/octet-stream"/>
      <category>Bill Summary</category>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>H.R. 788</title>
      <link>https://www.govtrack.us/congress/bills/118/hr788/summary</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.govtrack.us/congress/bills/118/hr788/summary</guid>
      <pubDate>Fri, 26 Jan 2024 11:25:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <description> 		 			&lt;h4 class="event_title"&gt;Bill Summary&lt;/h4&gt; 			&lt;div class="event_body"&gt; 				&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.govtrack.us/congress/bills/118/hr788/summary" &gt;H.R. 788: Stop Settlement Slush Funds Act of 2023&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt; 			&lt;/div&gt; 		  		&lt;div class="event_date"&gt; 			&lt;span&gt;Date: &lt;/span&gt; 			 				Jan 26, 2024 11:25 a.m. 			 		&lt;/div&gt;  		 		 		&lt;div class="event_body"&gt; 			 			 			&lt;p&gt;Per the Library of Congress, this bill "...prohibits the federal government from entering into or enforcing a settlement agreement on behalf of the United States that provides for a payment to any person or entity other than the United States. The bill provides exceptions to allow payments that (1) remedy actual harm (including to the environment) caused by the party making the payment, or (2) constitute a payment for services rendered in connection with the case."&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;What that means in …&lt;/p&gt; 		&lt;/div&gt; </description>
      <media:content url="https://www.govtrack.us/congress/bills/118/hr788/thumbnail" type="application/octet-stream"/>
      <category>Bill Summary</category>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>H.R. 6830</title>
      <link>https://www.govtrack.us/congress/bills/118/hr6830/summary</link>
